channel.title: Network Card
channel.description:
As a couple of you may know, i had problems with my video card a long time ago :o Got all the drivers installed, including internet. However, after going back to winxp after going with vista and linux, apparently it doesn't detect my network card, all drivers are installed but it doesn't seem to detect it. WHAT DO I DO?
P.S: If i have to live with vista for 2 more minutes.. :P

Run it and crack it with keygen, and go to upload -> your operating system -> select any of the wireless network drivers -> right click on the wireless network driver on the list, and get its url by: right click -> Copy URL to clipboard -> Download Address 1 OR Download Address 2

Then, go to a computer with internet, paste the url on to it, download it, and install it to your comp with no networkz.
